<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1354] Configuring DBCP connection pool with connection properties breaks when user/pasword is specifed and javax.* configuration is set to DBCP Driver</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1354</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Property combination on openjpa.* works&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.ConnectionDriver&quot; value=&quot;org.apache.commons.dbcp.BasicDataSource&quot;/&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.ConnectionProperties&quot; value=&quot;DriverClassName=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver,Url=jdbc:mysql://localhost/test,Username=scott,Password=tiger,MaxActive=40&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But mixing them as&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;property name=&quot;javax.persistence.jdbc.driver&quot; value=&quot;org.apache.commons.dbcp.BasicDataSource&quot;/&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.ConnectionProperties&quot; value=&quot;DriverClassName=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver,Url=jdbc:mysql://localhost/test,Username=scott,Password=tiger,MaxActive=40&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;breaks because dbcp.BasicDataSource.getConnection(user, pwd) throws UnSupportedOperationException&lt;/p&gt;</description>
